description.narrative: Haiti - Malaria - Population Services International - PSI HQ. This program has the following goals: By 2020, local transmission of malaria is reduced to 0.. The objectives of this program are: By 2020, 100% of malaria cases are confirmed by RDT or microscopy according to the national protocol for the management of malaria.. By 2020, 100% of malaria cases (confirmed by RDT or microscopy) are treated according to the national protocol for the management of malaria.. By 2020, 100% of malaria transmission foci are identified and managed.. By 2020, 80% of the population in high risk strata know the modes of malaria transmission, use individual protective measures, and participate in community-based actions in the fight against malaria.. By 2020, strategic information on malaria in Haiti is available and enables efficient and targeted interventions.. By 2020, the managerial, administrative, technological, financial, and social changes identified in the malaria elimination phase plan are made within the national health system.
